      "Water deluge operations continued for extended period",
      "2-inch hose rigged from M/V Miss Jessica Faye to pump water from boat",
      "M/V Seacor Brave continued water spray operations",
      "BSEE conducted onsite investigation on May 3, 2021"
    ],
    "summary": "On May 2, 2021, at approximately 10:11 hours, a fire occurred on the unmanned, out-of-service ST-26 A/A-QTR fixed platform in South Timbalier Block 26, Lease OCS-G 01361, operated by Cox Operating, L.L.C. The fire was caused by lightning striking the Communications Tower and Communications Building during severe thunderstorms. The fire was intensified by hydrocarbons released from a nearby Dry Oil Tank that was damaged by intense heat, causing process piping to separate at welds. Multiple response vessels conducted water deluge operations for approximately 18 hours. The fire was completely extinguished by May 3, 2021. No injuries were reported. Total property damage was estimated at $2,000,000.",
